        {
          "severity": "PASS",
          "line_approx": 39,
          "issue": "CVaR formula: climateCVaR(transVaR, physVaR, rho) correctly maps to Trans + Phys + rho*Trans*Phys via engine. Formula is correct.",
          "fix": "N/A"
        },
        {
          "severity": "PASS",
          "line_approx": 41,
          "issue": "Division safety: totalVaR division uses guard `cvar.totalVaR > 0 ? ... : '0'` at lines 162-165. No unguarded division by AUM (AUM slider min=1000 so cannot be 0).",
          "fix": "N/A"
        },
        {
          "severity": "P1",
          "line_approx": 208,
          "issue": "LOSS DISTRIBUTION REFERENCE LINE: `<ReferenceLine x={`${(-cvar.pct).toFixed(2)}`}` uses negative cvar.pct as the x-coordinate, but cvar.pct is already a positive percentage (e.g. 8.7). So -cvar.pct = -8.7. The distribution data x-axis from buildDistribution() is centred on `-(cvar.totalVaR / aum * 100)` which is also negative (e.g. -8.7). The VaR line at x=-8.7 would land inside the distribution (at the mean), not at the left tail. The ReferenceLine should be at the left tail cutoff, which is mean - z*sigma. This causes the VaR reference line to visually misrepresent the VaR level on the loss distribution chart.",
          "fix": "The ReferenceLine x should be at `${(-cvar.pct * 1.5).toFixed(2)}` (approximate left tail for sigma-scaled distribution) or more precisely at `${(-(cvar.pct / z) * z + (cvar.pct)).toFixed(2)}` which simplifies to the distribution mean value. Better fix: remove the ReferenceLine from the distribution chart and add a shading fill for the tail region instead, or compute the exact VaR quantile x-coordinate as `${(-3 * Math.max(1, cvar.pct / (NQ[confidence] ?? NQ[95]))).toFixed(2)}`."
        },
        {
          "severity": "P1",
          "line_approx": 157,
          "issue": "INTERACTION TERM UI DESCRIPTION: UI text reads 'ρ·CVaR_transition·CVaR_physical / AUM' but the engine at climateCVaR() returns `trans_cvar + phys_cvar + rho * trans_cvar * phys_cvar` without dividing by AUM in the interaction term. The formula display adds '/ AUM' which does not match the engine implementation. The interaction term is rho * transVaR_$ * physVaR_$ (both already in $), making the interaction term dimensionally in $^2 which is incorrect. The ECB/NGFS methodology specifies the interaction as rho * (transVaR% * physVaR%) * AUM to stay in $ units.",
          "fix": "Correct the engine: climateCVaR should accept percentage-of-AUM inputs OR the formula should normalise: `trans_cvar + phys_cvar + rho * trans_cvar * phys_cvar / aum`. Remove '/ AUM' from UI description and fix dimension consistency."
        },
        {
          "severity": "PASS",
          "line_approx": 34,
          "issue": "Horizon scaling uses sqrt(T/10) — correct per NGFS/ECB square-root-of-time convention with 10yr base.",
          "fix": "N/A"
        },
        {
          "severity": "PASS",
          "line_approx": 35,
          "issue": "Confidence level scaling uses z_adj = NQ[confidence] / NQ[95] with nullish fallback — correct.",
          "fix": "N/A"
        }
