          "issue": "NON-COMPLIANT PRNG: ILO pillar scores use `Math.round(40 + Math.sin(i * 1.5 + ILO_PILLARS.indexOf(p)) * 30 + 7.5 * (Math.sin(i * 3.7 + ILO_PILLARS.indexOf(p) * 2.1) + 1))`. Per audit rules, ALL pseudo-random generation MUST use the canonical seeded PRNG: `const sr = (s) => { let x = Math.sin(s+1)*10000; return x - Math.floor(x); }`. The current implementation uses raw Math.sin() with different scaling constants (multiplier 10000 and floor extraction is the canonical pattern — this code omits both, using direct sin output scaled by 30/7.5). This is a P1 PRNG compliance failure.",
          "fix": "Add `const sr = (s) => { let x = Math.sin(s+1)*10000; return x - Math.floor(x); };` at module top and replace score generation with: `score: Math.round(40 + sr(i * 5 + ILO_PILLARS.indexOf(p)) * 60)`"
