        "line_approx": 113,
        "issue": "historicalCVaR: `const varVal = -sorted[cutoff] ?? 0` — operator precedence bug. `-sorted[cutoff] ?? 0` evaluates as `(-sorted[cutoff]) ?? 0`. If sorted[cutoff] is undefined, -undefined = NaN and NaN ?? 0 = NaN (NaN is not null/undefined, so ?? does not catch it). varVal becomes NaN and propagates to cvarVal.",
        "fix": "Change to: `const varVal = sorted[cutoff] !== undefined ? -sorted[cutoff] : 0;`"
      }
    ]
